Step 1: Identify the revenue line item:
- Main Business Revenue / Total Revenue: 547,392.30

Step 2: Identify the cost line item:
- Cost of Goods Sold / Total Cost: 353,220.00

Step 3: Calculate the difference (revenue - cost):
547,392.30 - 353,220.00 = 194,172.30

Step 4: Verify if this matches any line item:
Yes, Gross Profit is 194,172.30 which matches the difference.

Therefore, the "value" is "194172.30".
